Hi Mikkel,

Not 100% sure but this may be solved by forward declaring templates. 
To demonstrate here is some code I ripped copied from a forum:


---------------------------------------------
// forward-declare a template
template&lt;class T&gt; struct A;
// forward-declare the operator
template&lt;class T&gt; ostream& operator&lt;&lt;(ostream& s, const A&lt;T&gt;&);

template&lt;class T&gt; struct A
{
    T t;

    // make it a friend
    friend ostream& operator &lt;&lt; &lt;T&gt;(ostream&, const A&lt;T&gt;&);
};

// now define it
template&lt;class T&gt;
ostream& operator &lt;&lt; (ostream& s,  const A&lt;T&gt;&)
{
    return s;
}
---------------------------------------------

I think this and the namespace issue Ken pointed out are both the 
result of later versions of GCC being more strict than previous 
versions.

Colin.
